/-- An linear map `f : M →ₗ[R] M₂` with a left-inverse `g : M₂ →ₗ[R] M` defines a linear
equivalence between `M` and `f.range`.

This is a computable alternative to `linear_equiv.of_injective`, and a bidirectional version of
